<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-636-112  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 636 112.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  August 28 1989 v217 n10 p28(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Big business drives U.K. local fiber. (lightguide communications)(a related article discusses residential fiber in the U.K.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Williamson, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The United Kingdom currently has one of the world's most dynamiclightguide communications industries.andP;  Research is generating asteady profusion of innovations.andP;  Commercial exploitation ofoptical fiber is likewise vigorous.andP;  As with the rest of theworld, however, fiber optical transmission has so far made littleimpact on the UK's local loop network.andP;  Costs have been a problem,but competitive supply is depressing fiber's price.andP;  Twoapplications could alter the status quo for local fiber in the UK.andO;One application is cable television, piggybacked with interactivetelecommunications services.andP;  The other is flexible access,designed initially for large business users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber opticsUnited KingdomTelephone companiesTelecommunicationsIndustry Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>